{"title": "China is itching to mine the ocean floor", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-07-31", "content": "Scattered across the ocean floor are trillions of lumps of nickel, copper, cobalt and manganese. Companies have long wanted to mine them: These \u201ccritical minerals\u201d are needed in vast quantities to electrify the global economy and cut dependence on fossil fuels.\nBut the International Seabed Authority (ISA), a UN body, is still figuring out how mining should be regulated. Some environmental groups want an outright ban."}